abstract: The steam-ship Waesland, of the Red Star Line, arrived from Antwerp yesterday after a tempestuous voyage of 22 days. She sailed on Nov. 12, and on the 15th a heavy westerly gale was encountered. Seas broke over the decks, stove in the doors of the steerage companionway, and smashed the skylight of the second cabin. On the 18th it blew a hurricane, and the ship labored fearfully in the tremendous sea that was then on.

abstract: DETROIT, Mich., Dec. 5.--An old German milk vendor named Christian Ternes was brutally murdered last night by Charles Martin, a young iron-molder. Martin was drunk, and, teasing Ternes on the street, received an impatient response, whereupon he knocked Ternes down and kicked and stamped upon him until his skull was crushed. Martin was arrested, but pretends that he knows nothing about the murder.

abstract: Large numbers of Socialists have recently been expelled from three important German towns. Many have gone to England to seek new homes, and many have come to these shores. Four of them had been in the German Parliament.
